      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Constraint — proposal\n\n**Purpose**: A boundary that implementation must respect.\n\n**Canonical fields**:\n- `label` (string)\n- `body` (markdown)\n- `category` (schema | ux | performance | policy | security)\n- `hardness` (hard | soft)\n- `scope` (global | subgraph | node-local)\n\n**Rules**:\n- Hard constraints are never negotiable without a Decision node.\n- Soft constraints are guidance; Codex may deviate with explanation.\n- Constraint is a **node**, not an edge. It connects via `constrains` edges to what it governs.\n- Open question: does a global constraint need special handling in fragment traversal?",
        "memo": "",
        "link": "",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
