          "dataType": "any",
          "position": {
            "side": "left",
            "offset": 0.5
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "out",
          "label": "Out",
          "direction": "output",
          "dataType": "any",
          "position": {
            "side": "right",
            "offset": 0.5
          }
        }
      ],
      "inputs": [
        {
          "key": "in",
          "label": "In",
          "type": "any"
        }
      ],
      "outputs": [
        {
          "key": "out",
          "label": "Out",
          "type": "any"
        }
      ],
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Dependency — proposal\n\n**Resolution**: Both node and edge, with distinct roles.\n\n- **Edge-only** (`depends-on` edge type): sufficient for simple ordering — A must complete before B.\n- **Node** (this type): use when the dependency is a first-class entity — an external system, a prerequisite artifact, a third-party service, or a blocker with its own status.\n\n**Canonical fields** (node form):\n- `label` (string)\n- `body` (markdown)\n- `kind` (external-system | prerequisite | blocker | ordering)\n- `status` (pending | available | blocked | resolved)\n- `source` (string — what provides this dependency)\n\n**Rules**:\n- Prefer edge for pure ordering. Use node when status, source, or kind matter.\n- A blocker dependency with `status: blocked` should surface in prompt context.",
        "memo": "",
        "link": "",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
