          "type": "content"
        }
      ],
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Arch: Constraint as node\n\n**Decision**: Constraint is a first-class node, not edge metadata.\n\nRationale: constraints need independent identity, category, hardness, and scope. They connect to what they govern via typed `constrains` edges. Edge-only representation loses too much.\n\nOpen: global-scope constraint behavior in fragment traversal is deferred.",
        "memo": "",
        "link": "",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
